com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"':'\"$INGRESS_NODE_IP\"' \\\n    https://demo.example.com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"'/'\n```\n\nNote: use the CA override (--cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt) for validation.\nopenssl is available via the toolbox pod:\n```bash\nkubectl -n demo exec openssl-toolbox -- openssl version\n```\n\nDiagnose the TLS issue and restore HTTPS access to the service.\nSuccess criteria: the curl command returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
