{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014dK8QuCxSumpK7JKYHAEz3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture! The precondition:\n1. Generated a CA key at `/tmp/test-ca.key`\n2. Created a CA cert from that key (saved as `/tmp/test-ca.crt`)\n3. Created an **expired** leaf cert signed by that CA (startdate=20200101, enddate=20200102 - expired in 2020!)\n4. Created the `expired-tls-secret` with that expired cert\n5. Created the `test-ca` configmap with the CA cert (`/tmp/test-ca.crt`)\n6. The curl-test pod mounts the CA cert\n7. Now I need to generate a fresh valid leaf cert for `demo.example.com` using the CA key and cert, then update the `expired-tls-secret` with it\n\nBut I should double-check that the CA cert in the configmap matches the one the pod is actually using, since there might be a mismatch between what was created and what's mounted.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8800,"cache_read_input_tokens":46838,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8800},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba01a375-ceae-4928-8bf1-2a0238ef7b36","uuid":"ebef5860-348c-4d31-b28b-fbc4f25ecf3b","request_id":"req_011CcQVRn5smdAzmMYtco4BE"}
