k mentions TLS certificate validation errors, the primary issue is the expired certificate, but the ingress also won't be processed because of this class mismatch. I should fix both—renew the TLS secret and reassign the ingress to use the correct controller class. The ingress class name likely changed during the upgrade, so the `demo-ingress` is pointing to a controller that's no longer active. I need to figure out which controller is actually listening on port 30108 to understand what's handling the traffic now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":648,"cache_read_input_tokens":63651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":648},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba01a375-ceae-4928-8bf1-2a0238ef7b36","uuid":"1fc62b45-5b5a-4eb0-855a-ed4f35ff538a","request_id":"req_011CcQVaNG9wvqQzAgi5mPcU"}
