{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019oYuPBcLKiGSreQNpDn7Wg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The controller now picked up the `demo-ingress` (it shows \"creating ingress demo/demo-ingress ingressclass=ingress-1\"). But there's a warning:\n\n`Error getting SSL certificate \"demo/expired-tls-secret\": local SSL certificate demo/expired-tls-secret was not found. Using default certificate`\n\nThis means the controller picked up the ingress but it's using the default cert because the `expired-tls-secret` wasn't loaded yet when the ingress was first processed. But wait, I already updated the secret with a new cert. Let me check the timing.\nActually, the issue is that nginx-ingress tried to load the TLS cert when processing the ingress, but even though I updated the secret, the cert hadn't synced to the local store yet. The nginx config reload probably happened before that sync completed. It should catch up in a few seconds, so let me wait and test again.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1097,"cache_read_input_tokens":67577,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1097},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba01a375-ceae-4928-8bf1-2a0238ef7b36","uuid":"c3e39ae8-c60f-45b2-800c-9f57e83818fd","request_id":"req_011CcQVfEvXJWjvVxUv4Q8RQ"}
