{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LA4EnXHdkFRkWmUdhrQ4J1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is working. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\nHere's what was wrong and what I fixed:\n\n**Root cause — two issues:**\n\n1. **Expired TLS certificate** — `expired-tls-secret` contained a cert valid only from Jan 1–2, 2020 (expired >6 years ago). I generated a new 2-year cert for `demo.example.com` signed by the Test CA (`/tmp/test-ca.key` + `/tmp/test-ca.crt`) and updated the secret.\n\n2. **Wrong IngressClass** — `demo-ingress` referenced `ingressClassName: nginx`, but after the nginx ingress upgrade, no controller handles the `nginx` IngressClass. The active controller on port 30108 uses `ingress-1`. I patched the ingress to `ingressClassName: ingress-1`.\n\n**Verification:** `curl --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt` returns HTTP 200 with body `hello`, `SSL certificate verify ok`, certificate CN=demo.example.com valid until Jun 24 2028."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1842,"cache_read_input_tokens":68674,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1842},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba01a375-ceae-4928-8bf1-2a0238ef7b36","uuid":"8454a2cc-35c9-452c-ab60-2ecabdfa0d11","request_id":"req_011CcQVgBQiSjB8ZV3bTgLYN"}
